@startuml togaf-overview
!theme plain
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

title TOGAF Architecture Overview - WhatsChat Messaging System

package "Business Architecture" as BA {
  component [Business Actors] as Actors
  component [Business Capabilities] as Capabilities
  component [Business Processes] as Processes
  component [Business Value] as Value
  note right of BA
    **business-architecture.puml**
    User management, instant messaging,
    feed & posts, Reels, follow, recommendations & explore,
    content moderation, comments, engagement (like/save),
    voice & video calls, file sharing, groups, contacts,
    notifications, admin dashboard, advertising & monetization
  end note
}

package "Application Architecture" as AA {
  component [Client Applications] as Clients
  component [API Gateways] as Gateways
  component [Application Services] as Services
  component [Data Access] as DataAccess
  note right of AA
    **application-architecture.puml**
    Web/Mobile/Admin, REST/GraphQL/WebSocket/WebRTC,
    NestJS (Post, Feed, Explore, Comment, Follow, Search, engagement,
    Admin recheck/hide/batch delete, Ads serving/targeting/pacing + Ads Admin APIs),
    Python Recommendation (Celery, LightFM, Redis, ad ETL/metrics),
    Vision (Python, NudeNet, ResNet50). Admin: AG Grid, Recharts, i18n, Ads pages.
  end note
}

package "Data Architecture" as DA {
  component [Data Entities] as Entities
  component [Association Entities] as Associations
  component [Data Storage] as Storage
  note right of DA
    **data-architecture.puml**
    User/Chat/Message/Group/Call/Status,
    Post (mediaUrls, coverUrl)/FeedEntry/Comment/Engagement,
    moderationStatus, hidden (ES), Contact/Notification/FileUpload, Follow,
    AdAccount/AdCampaign/AdGroup/AdCreative/AdSpend, AnalyticsEvent (incl. ads),
    PostgreSQL, Redis, Cassandra, MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Kafka
  end note
}

package "Technology Architecture" as TA {
  component [Client Technology Stack] as ClientTech
  component [Server Technology Stack] as ServerTech
  component [Data Persistence] as Persistence
  component [Deployment Infrastructure] as Deploy
  note right of TA
    **technology-architecture.puml**
    Next.js, React Native, NestJS, Python (recommendation, Vision),
    Prisma, JWT, Celery, Cassandra, MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Redis, Docker,
    LightFM, implicit, Annoy, NudeNet, ResNet50, OpenCV
  end note
}

BA -down-> AA : drives
AA -down-> DA : depends on
DA -down-> TA : supported by

note bottom
  **TOGAF Four Architecture Domains**
  Business architecture defines WhatsChat business capabilities and processes;
  application architecture implements Web/Mobile clients and backend services;
  data architecture describes entities, storage, and data flows;
  technology architecture defines the technology stack and deployment.
  See each domain's .puml diagram for details.
end note

@enduml
